      "content": "The silence you feel is a common sign that your mind and body are struggling to adapt to a major loss or change. It is a natural response to grief, and allowing yourself to feel that emptiness can help you begin to process what has happened. While the house may feel unfamiliar, your presence there is still meaningful, even if the routine has changed. Consider reaching out to a trusted friend or a professional counselor who can offer support during this difficult transition.",
