    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but it's not meaningful. it's just... empty. the meaning was in him. without him, everything is just repetitive motions. i eat, i sleep, i stare at his side of the bed. it feels like i'm just performing a role in a play that closed months ago. i don't see the point in pretending there's something left to find.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It is incredibly painful when the world loses its purpose around you, and feeling like a stranger in your own life is a heavy burden to carry. While you are right that the old meaning is gone, consider that your grief is a valid form of mourning rather than a failure to find new meaning immediately. You do not have to force yourself to find something new right now; simply acknowledging that you are lost is an important first step in healing.",
      "source": "target",
